{"type":"message","id":"678cff31","parentId":"06f9c4ab","timestamp":"2026-06-27T03:09:31.592Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The MCP service is running and processing requests, but there's a critical issue: \"failed to load cookies: failed to read cookies from tmp file: open cookies.json: no such file or directory\". This means the MCP service doesn't have valid cookies/login, so the search is failing.\n\nThe service needs to be logged in to search小红书. Since the cookies file doesn't exist, it seems like we need to log in first. But this is running in a Docker container, so I can't easily do the QR code login.\n\nHowever, I notice the script `xiaohongshu_push_v3.py` might have its own fallback or might be able to get content without login (the MediaCrawler MCP on port 18080 might be an alternative). Let me check if MediaCrawler MCP is running on port 18080."},{"type":"text","text":"MCP 缺少登录 cookie，搜索会失败。检查 MediaCrawler MCP（端口 18080）是否可用：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6e73a5f977b84f4496b21f27","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"http://localhost:18080/sse\" -TimeoutSec 5 2>&1 | Select-Object StatusCode"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782529764555}}
